16/06/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- One soldier died on Wednesday (June 16th) in the latest clash between the army and members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) -- this one in Sirnak province.
On Tuesday, another soldier died and three others were injured when a homemade bomb exploded in the same province.
The bomb was apparently planted by the PKK near a border patrol not far from Iraq.
(Hurriyet - 16/06/10;
AFP, CNN Turk - 15/06/10)
